dcterms:description: MovingMNIST consists of 5000 sequences of 20 images, where each image displays a moving white number on a black background. It is used to evaluate representations learned by video prediction models.
dcterms:title: MovingMNIST

dcterms:description: The fMRI dataset is a subset of 62 subjects from the MPILMBB resting-state dataset, where participants were measured at rest with eyes-open. The dataset includes preprocessed and denoised fMRI signals parcellated on 523 non-overlapping ROIs.
dcterms:title: fMRI dataset (subset of MPILMBB resting-state dataset)
